ent action code); (e) CheckTalkTree m_CurrentNPC null-guard removal at PlayerConnection.cpp:10582 (would null-deref through to GenerateTalkTree and SEGV on this exact payload); (f) SendTalkTreeAction Wave 11 sizeof(long) regression at PlayerConnection.cpp:7767 (int32_t action_wire cast pins width to 4B; revert would emit 8B with top 4 garbage on Linux x86_64 — caught immediately by length assertion); (g) server→client 0x0056 forwarding regression in proxy SendClientPacketSequence. Per CLAUDE.md server-integrity: the wire shape is exactly what retail Win32 client emits when user clicks the X on a TalkTree dialog; the SendTalkTreeAction(-32) close-display sentinel is verbatim retail behaviour for SELECT_TALK_TREE with Selection=0 and no current NPC."),
